In this speech given at the Future Farmers of America (FFA) Convention, President Trump addresses the recent shooting at a synagogue in Pittsburgh and condemns anti-Semitism and religious hatred. He also discusses his administration's efforts to support farmers and improve trade deals, highlighting the importance of American agriculture. The President emphasizes the need for hard work and perseverance, and recognizes the winners of the American Star Award, who are FFA members making significant contributions in their fields. He concludes by expressing his belief in the future of American farmers and their ability to make America great again.